1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

The target image shows a small house-like structure built from various rectangular and triangular blocks.  There are 7 blocks total, in 3 layers.  The structure is symmetrical, with two orange rectangular blocks forming the main vertical support, and one green rectangular block on either side.  A blue rectangular block is above the orange and green, creating a gap in the middle, and an orange triangular block sits atop the blue and orange.  A second orange triangular block is on the opposing side, completing the roof structure.


2. **Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

| Block Index | Description                       |
|-------------|-----------------------------------|
| 3           | Orange rectangular block             |
| 2           | Green rectangular block            |
| 6           | Blue rectangular block             |
| 13         | Orange triangular block (pointed left)|
| 15         | Orange triangular block (pointed right) |


3. **Determine the Assembly Order:**

```json
{
  "Step1": "Move block with index 3",
  "Step2": "Move block with index 2 to the left of block 3",
  "Step3": "Move block with index 3 again, to the right of block 2",
  "Step4": "Move block with index 6 on top of block 3 (and 2)",
  "Step5": "Move block with index 13 on top of the block 6",
  "Step6": "Move block with index 2 on the left side of block 6,  then right next to the block 3",
  "Step7": "Move block with index 15 on the right side of block 6, next to block 3"
}
```
